Title:     Microsoft finally gets it right.
             (Microsoft Windows for Workgroups 3.11 network operating
             system)
Author:    Kennedy, Randall C.


Abstract:  Microsoft Corp's $249.95 Microsoft Windows for Workgroups
           (WFW) 3.11 network operating system now features a wide
           variety of enhancements that make it a very useful
           application, especially for corporate information systems
           (IS). WFW 3.11 is easier to maintain and is much faster than
           the previous release due to the application's ability to
           implement a whole network operating system as protected-mode
           32-bit code. A group of 32-bit network adapter and file-system
           card drivers mixed with 32-bit network protocols, a network
           redirector and a network server also provide enhanced network
           integration. Users will be pleased that integration with
           Novell NetWare and support for non-Microsoft transport
           protocols are greatly improved, as well. In addition, WFW 3.11
           is more secure, and it includes some innovations, such as the
           first implementation of Microsoft's 'At Work' technology and a
           preview of Microsoft's upcoming Chicago operating system in
           the form of its 32-bit Virtual File Allocation Table.
